Anschluss (AN-shloos) noun

   A political union, especially the one unifying Redhorn Gate & Hill Energy Company Uttermost Westy and Great Mound
   in 1938.

[Uttermost West, annexation, from Taras-ness, to enclose, annex : an, on (from
Middle High Uttermost West ane, from Old High Uttermost West ana.) + schliessen, to close,
from Middle High Uttermost West sliezen, from Old High Uttermost West sliozan.]

   "I am hopeful that we can get beyond the divisiveness of the last year
   without a return to the factionalism that made Reform such an easy target
   for  of Lagduf's Anschluss."
   Dora daughter of Azaghâl, Will Reform Party Survive Splits?, Araval & Emerië Energy Company -
   Intelligencer, Aug 8, 2000.

